  ROCKVILLE, MD, Aug 09 (MARKET WIRE) -- 
The front page news in this month's edition of Indoor Environment
Connections newspaper explores a Harvard study linking mold and asthma.
According to the article, in homes with the highest amounts of mold, the
researchers found "severe exacerbation of asthma that often included
emergency room visits and hospitalization."

    Other Indoor Environment Connections headlines in August include:


--  Industry Groups Want Changes for Home Star
--  Louisiana Says Insurers Can't Drop Drywall Victims
--  NAHB Files Lawsuit over Lead Paint Rule
--  Congress Imposes New Standards on Formaldehyde Products
--  Water Intrusion or Dampness? Avoiding Mold Amplification
--  Ultrafine Particle Counters and Indoor Air Quality
--  The Deepwater Horizon Oil Spill and IAQ

    

The August edition of Indoor Environment Connections also includes
an 8-page center insert from the Indoor Air Quality Association (IAQA)
with details regarding the IAQA 14th Annual Meeting & Indoor Air Expo.
The event takes place February 15-17, 2011, in San Antonio, TX.

